In article <1994Jun6.185335.16654@imag.fr>,
Marc Samama <samama@imag.imag.fr> wrote:
>I'd like to know how hard it is to find a text for wich 'sum' will
>give the same hash value, particularly if i want the text to
>resemble a given text. 
>
>Is there any article that discusses a method to do that?
>-- 
I don't know of an article that discusses how, but it is very easy.
'sum' does not make any effort at all to be hard to defeat on purpose.
It is only suppose to give a safeguard against random errors.
If you just look at a description of its algorithm (in the POSIX
standard, say), the method of doing what you want should be
apparent.

